               <occupation type="literary"> secretary </occupation>
               
               
               
               <floruit notBefore="1868" notAfter="1900">He was one of the two secretaries of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/>.
                  In the court of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/>, he was an indispensible assistant to the emepror. 
                  While <roleName type="title">Ṣaḥāfe tǝʿǝzāz</roleName> <persName ref="PRS4359Gabrase"/> was in charge of the home affairs and the correspondence in Amharic,
                  Yosef thanks to his knowledge of French, was responsible for relation with foreigners and served <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/> as a kind of foreign secretary. 
                  In <date>1889</date>, he involved in the translation of the Amharic version of  Italo-Ethiopian Treaty of Freindship and Commerce. 
                  
                    </floruit>
               
               <death when="1900">He died at <placeName ref="LOC2976Entott"/> in <date>1900</date>.</death>
               
